    <section id="AuthorsGuidelinessec" class="padding">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="section-title reveal">Author's Guidelines</h2>

        <!-- Introduction -->
        <div class="row justify-content-center mb-5">
          <div class="col-lg-10">
            <div class="card shadow-sm border-0 mb-4 reveal reveal--scale">
              <div class="card-body p-5">
                <ol class="mb-3" style="line-height: 1.8; text-align: justify">
                  <li class="mb-3">
                    <strong>Scope and Originality</strong>
                    <br />
                    All submissions must present original, unpublished work that
                    is not under consideration elsewhere. Manuscripts must fall
                    within the scope and objectives of the conference/journal.
                  </li>
                  <li class="mb-3">
                    <strong>Author Eligibility</strong>
                    <br />
                    Submissions are invited from academicians, researchers,
                    industry professionals, research scholars, and students.
                    Student submissions are encouraged and may include faculty
                    co-authorship. No minimum publication experience is
                    required, provided academic standards are met.
                  </li>
                  <li class="mb-3">
                    <strong>Language Requirements</strong>
                    <br />
                    Manuscripts must be written in clear and grammatically
                    correct English. Authors must use American English, but
                    consistency must be maintained throughout the paper.
                  </li>
                  <li class="mb-3">
                    <strong>Plagiarism Policy</strong>
                    <br />
                    All submissions will be screened using plagiarism detection
                    software.
                    <ul style="margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 8px">
                      <li>
                        Maximum permissible similarity: 10% overall, excluding
                        references.
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        Manuscripts exceeding the limit may be rejected or
                        returned for revision.
                      </li>
                    </ul>
                    Plagiarism in any form is strictly prohibited.
                  </li>
                  <li class="mb-3">
                    <strong>Peer Review Process</strong>
                    <br />
                    Each submission will undergo a peer review process.
                    Decisions may include acceptance, acceptance with revisions,
                    or rejection. The decision of the reviewer's team is final
                    and binding.
                  </li>
                  <li class="mb-3">
                    <strong>Registration and Fees</strong>
                    <br />
                    For accepted papers, at least one author must register.
                    Registration fees are mandatory and non-refundable and must
                    be paid within the stipulated deadline to ensure for
                    presentation of paper in the conference. Publication charges
                    will be separately applicable.
                  </li>
                  <li class="mb-3">
                    <strong>Presentation and Attendance</strong>
                    <br />
                    For conferences, at least one registered author must present
                    the paper. Failure to present may result in removal from the
                    final proceedings. Outside Mumbai authors may present
                    through online mode.
                  </li>
                </ol>
                <br />
                <p class="mb-3">
